  "abstract": "Blister beetles of the subfamily Meloidao are widely known as flower beetles or\r\npollen beetles feeding on cereals, grain legumes and Malvaceae(Hill  1983).\r\nGenera involved are: Psalydolytta, My labris, Decapotoma, Coryna, Cyl indrothorax,\r\nCyanopytta etc . Several species of these genera have been observed on millet\r\n(Pennisetum g laucum (L.)R. Br.)heads in the Sahel (Magema and Dalhove 1985,…………………………………\r\n",
